          <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">How to claim</h1>

          <p class="govuk-body">You can apply for Attendance Allowance online or by post.</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">To apply, you will need:</p>

          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>your National Insurance number</li>
            <li>details of health condition and disabilties that mean you need extra help or care</li>
            <li>your GP surgery or medical centre details</li>
            <li>your address and contact details</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-static-padding-top-5">Apply online</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">This is a new service. Only a limited number of people can apply online each week.</p>

          <a href="who-is-applying" role="button" draggable="false" class="govuk-button govuk-button--start" data-module="govuk-button">
            Start now
            <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <path fill="currentColor" d="M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z" />
          </svg></a>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-static-padding-top-5">Apply by post</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">To apply by post, either:</p>

          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>print and submit a  <a href="#" class="govuk-link">paper claim form</a></li>
            <li>contact the helpline to get one posted to you</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="govuk-inset-text">
            If you live in Northern Ireland, there is a different way to apply for <a href="#" class="govuk-link">Attendance Allowance</a>.
          </div>

          <p class="govuk-body">Send the completed form to:</p>

          <div style="border-left: 1px solid #b1b4b6; padding-left: 15px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-top: 30px;">
            <p class="govuk-body">Freepost</br>
            DWP Attendance Allowance</p>
          </div>

          <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-7">You do not need a postcode or a stamp.</p>

          <div style="border-left: 1px solid #b1b4b6; padding-left: 15px; margin-bottom: 30px; margin-top: 30px;">
            <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Attendance Allowance helpline</p>
            <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Telephone: 0800 731 0122</p>
            <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Textphone: 0800 731 0317</p>
            <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0"><a href="#" class="govuk-link">Relay UK</a> (if you cannot hear or speak on the phone): 18001 then 0800 731 0122</p>
            <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">British Sign Language (BSL) <a href="#" class="govuk-link">video relay service</a> 
            if you’re on a computer - find out how to <a href="#" class="govuk-link">use the service on mobile or tablet</a></p>
            <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Monday to Friday, 8am to 6pm</p>
            <p class="govuk-body "><a href="#" class="govuk-link">Find out about call charges</a></p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-static-padding-top-5">When you’ll be paid</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">If you’re awarded Attendance Allowance, it can be paid from the start of your claim. It cannot be backdated.</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">If you print and post the form, or apply online, your claim will start on the date the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) receives it.</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">If you call the helpline to request a form, your claim will start on the date of your call (if you return the form within 6 weeks).</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">After you’ve applied, you’ll get a text or letter within 3 weeks that explains how long it’ll take to get a decision. 
          Once the decision has been made, you’ll get a letter explaining the outcome. If you’ve been awarded Attendance Allowance, 
          this will tell you when you’ll get your first payment.</p>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-static-padding-top-5">If you might have 12 months or less to live</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">You can get Attendance Allowance more quickly if a medical professional has said you might have 
          12 months or less to live. This is sometimes called ‘special rules’.</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">You must complete an <a href="what-youll-get" class="#">paper claim form</a>. 
          You should also ask a doctor or medical professional for form SR1 - they’ll either 
          fill it in and give the form to you or send it directly to the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP).</p>

          <p class="govuk-body">You can do this on behalf of someone else without their permission. The letter about the money awarded will not mention ‘special rules’.</p>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-static-padding-top-5">If you disagree with a decision</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">You can <a href="what-youll-get" class="#">challenge a decision</a> about your claim. 
          This is called asking for mandatory reconsideration.</p>

          <h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-static-padding-top-5">Complaints</h2>

          <p class="govuk-body">You can <a href="what-youll-get" class="#">complain to DWP</a> if you’re unhappy with the service you’ve received.</p>
        
